Quote: One or two five- or six-feet members of the finny [t]ribe were caught by caterers for the camp at School Bay, and it is reported that " Pelorus Jack" has forsaken his old haunt outside the Heads, where for many months he has patiently awaited a victim, to forage in Queen Charlotte Sound; at any rate passengers from Nelson to Picton no longer see the curious creature disporting itself at the heads, and, so the story goes, a huge black fin like a cross cut saw leaves a long wake in divers places in the Sound.
