Quote: While many believed he was guiding ships safely through the treacherous waters of French Pass, Mr Webber said Pelorus Jack didn't enter the pass at all... For Maori, the dolphin's history goes even further back than the 1880s. It is believed Pelorus Jack, known as Kaikaiawaro (food of the deep) to Maori, escorted descendants of Ngati Kuia into Pelorus Sound hundreds of years later.
